---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout title="What Temperature is a Fever? C vs F Reference" description="What temperature is a fever? Normal ranges in Celsius and Fahrenheit for adults and children with clear thresholds." keywords="fever temperature, normal body temperature, fever celsius, fever fahrenheit, what is a fever, body temperature chart, fever in children">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-600">Blog</a> <span class="mx-1">›</span> <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Temperature</span>
      </nav>
      <BlogCrossLinks title="What Temperature is a Fever? °C vs °F Reference" />
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">June 20, 2025 • 4 min read</p>

      <p>Your thermometer reads 38.2°C or maybe 101°F — is that a fever? Understanding fever thresholds in both Celsius and Fahrenheit helps you make informed health decisions, especially when reading advice from different countries.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Normal Body Temperature</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-5 my-6 not-prose">
        <p class="text-center text-lg font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">Normal: 36.1-37.2°C (97-99°F)</p>
        <p class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">Average: 37°C (98.6°F) — but this varies person to person</p>
      </div>
      <p>The often-quoted 98.6°F (37°C) dates from 1851. Modern research suggests average body temperature has actually decreased slightly to around 36.6°C (97.9°F), likely due to reduced chronic infections and changes in living conditions.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Fever Thresholds</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Low-grade fever:</strong> 37.3-38.0°C (99.1-100.4°F)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Fever:</strong> 38.0°C+ (100.4°F+) — this is the medical threshold</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>High fever:</strong> 39.4°C+ (103°F+)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Dangerous/Emergency:</strong> 40°C+ (104°F+) — seek immediate medical help</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Fever Thresholds in Children</h2>
      <p>Children have slightly different guidelines depending on age and measurement method:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Rectal (most accurate for infants):</strong> fever at 38°C (100.4°F) or above</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Oral:</strong> fever at 37.8°C (100°F) or above</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Armpit:</strong> fever at 37.2°C (99°F) or above (less reliable)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Ear:</strong> fever at 38°C (100.4°F) or above</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>For infants under 3 months, any temperature of 38°C (100.4°F) or higher warrants a call to the doctor regardless of symptoms.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Why Body Temperature Varies</h2>
      <p>Normal body temperature fluctuates throughout the day and between individuals:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Time of day:</strong> lowest in early morning (around 36.2°C), highest in late afternoon (up to 37.5°C)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>After exercise:</strong> can temporarily rise 1-2°C</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Menstrual cycle:</strong> rises 0.3-0.6°C after ovulation</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Age:</strong> older adults tend to run slightly cooler</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Method:</strong> oral, rectal, ear, and forehead readings differ by up to 0.6°C</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Quick Conversion for Medical Temperatures</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>37.0°C = 98.6°F (normal average)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>37.5°C = 99.5°F (elevated)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>38.0°C = 100.4°F (fever threshold)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>38.5°C = 101.3°F</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>39.0°C = 102.2°F</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>39.5°C = 103.1°F (high fever)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>40.0°C = 104.0°F (seek medical attention)</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>This information is for general reference only. Always consult a healthcare professional for medical advice regarding fevers, especially in infants, elderly individuals, or immunocompromised patients.</p>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-10 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Try It Now</h3>
        <a href="/convert/temperature" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 text-white text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors">Open Temperature Converter →</a>
      </div>
    
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 p-4 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">🔗 Try our converter: <a href="/convert/temperature" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 font-bold hover:underline">Open Converter →</a></p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
